    <string name="calibration_guide_content">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>Why Calibration Matters</b><br/><br/>
        Calibration removes sensor drift and makes cursor movement, clicks, and scrolling more reliable.<br/><br/>
        <b>1. Gyroscope Calibration</b><br/>
        Place the phone flat on a stable table and do not touch it while the app measures the bias offset.<br/><br/>
        <b>2. Magnetometer Calibration</b><br/>
        Slowly move the phone through a wide figure‑8 pattern so it can sample the surrounding magnetic field from multiple angles.<br/><br/>
        <b>3. Accelerometer Calibration</b><br/>
        Put the phone flat again and keep it still so the app can capture the gravity reference used for motion detection.<br/><br/>
        <b>4. Completion</b><br/>
        When the progress bar reaches 100%, return to the Home screen and press Start. If the room has strong magnetic noise, repeat calibration once more.
        ]]>
    </string>
