    <string name="help_content">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>Quick Start</b><br/><br/>
        1. Install and run the Air Mouse server on your PC.<br/>
        2. Make sure both devices are connected to the same Wi‑Fi network.<br/>
        3. Enter the PC IP address or scan the QR code from the server.<br/>
        4. Calibrate the sensors before the first session.<br/>
        5. Tap <b>Start Air Mouse</b> and adjust sensitivity if needed.<br/><br/>
        <b>Air Mouse Controls</b><br/><br/>
        • <b>Move cursor</b>: Rotate the phone smoothly to move the pointer.<br/>
        • <b>Left click</b>: Perform a short quick flick gesture.<br/>
        • <b>Right click</b>: Tilt the phone to the configured right-click angle.<br/>
        • <b>Double click</b>: Perform two quick click gestures in succession.<br/>
        • <b>Scroll up/down</b>: Move the phone vertically with a faster, shorter motion.<br/><br/>
        <b>Practical Tips</b><br/>
        • Keep the phone steady during calibration and while not actively moving the cursor.<br/>
        • Start with medium sensitivity, then increase it only if the pointer feels slow.<br/>
        • If gestures feel delayed, check Wi‑Fi quality and keep the phone close to the PC.<br/>
        • Use the drawer to open calibration, statistics, logs, and the advanced tools.
        ]]>
    </string>
